cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper focuses on evaluating topic models based on document-level topic allocations, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for predicting topic model quality, which involves machine learning techniques and statistical analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with data analysis and modeling, which is a common theme in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
